<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="581" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[112,648,566,749]" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">
DIAGNOSIS. 
<emphasis box="[228,253,567,590]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">—</emphasis>
Among 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Robillard" authorityYear="2004" box="[333,434,566,590]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Lebinthini">Lebinthini</taxonomicName>
genera, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1878" box="[511,646,566,590]" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Cardiodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[511,646,566,590]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">Cardiodactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterised by its large size, long wings most often with whitish spots in both sexes, male FW venation (Wshaped harp veins, mirror incomplete generally elongated longitudinally), and male genitalia (pseudepiphallic dorso-lateral crests, posterior apex of pseudepiphallus more or less spoon-like).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="581" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[113,646,787,908]" box="[113,213,787,813]" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[113,646,787,908]" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">
